Azure pricing models determine how users are charged for services. Common models include:

* Pay-as-you-go
* Reserved instances
* Spot pricing

For example, pay-as-you-go allows users to pay only for what they use.

A real-life use case is startups using pay-as-you-go to minimize upfront costs.

Another example is enterprises using reserved instances to reduce long-term costs.

Understanding pricing models helps optimize spending and choose the best option.
